  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>ginger</strong> (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate)</p>\r\n<p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onions</strong> finely</p>\r\n<p>Strip the <strong>thyme leaves</strong> from the stalks and chop them finely (or if your stalks are soft, then just chop them up too)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>chicken stock cube</strong> in 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine the <strong>chicken stock</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>honey</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;chopped thyme</strong>, <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>ginger</strong> and half the <strong>spring onion</strong>&nbsp;(save the rest for later!) in a mixing bowl &ndash; this is your <strong>super</strong>&nbsp;<strong>marinade&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the<strong>&nbsp;Tenderstem broccoli </strong>into rough, bite-sized pieces &nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372__step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372__step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372__step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372__step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372__step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop the <strong>chicken thighs</strong> into thick strips</p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;them to a mixing bowl with the <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\">(Can't</span> handle the heat? Go easy!) and a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix well and set aside</p>\r\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken strips </strong>and cook for 5 min or until they're coloured</p>\r\n<p>Tip:&nbsp;don't overcrowd the pan with the&nbsp;<strong>chicken</strong> or it will sweat instead of brown</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/372.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>wheat noodles</strong> to a pan and cover them with <strong>boiled water</strong> until they're fully submerged</p>\r\n<p>Boil over a high heat for 5-7 min until cooked, then drain and set aside</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
